'''Ingwë''' was the King of the [[Vanyar]], and the High King of the Elves.<ref name="princes" /> 

==History==
Ingwë was one of the [[Minyar]] born at [[Cuiviénen]]. He was the eldest son of [[Ilion]], and a descendant of [[Imin]] and [[Iminyë]], from eldest son to eldest son. He was beloved by his people, and at some point before the [[Great Journey]] he wed [[Ilwen]] and had several children at Cuiviénen by the time [[Oromë]] found the [[Quendi]].<ref name="Gol">{{NM|P1xvii}}, pp. 127-128</ref> 

When Oromë invited them to [[Aman]], Ingwë, along with [[Finwë]] and [[Elwë Singollo|Elwë]], were the most eager to visit, and so followed him as ambassadors and travelled to the Blessed Realm. Once there, Ingwë desired to "dwell in the presence of Varda", and was reluctant to return to [[Middle-earth]].<ref name="Ard" />

When they returned, they held a [[Debate of the Quendi|great debate]], and told their peoples about its beauty and bliss and became their leaders during the [[Great March]]. Ingwë was the leader of the [[Vanyar]], the foremost of the clans to follow Oromë, who were the most eager to reach the [[West]], which they did quickly.<ref name="journey">{{S|3}}</ref>

After the [[Great Journey]], Ingwë never returned or set eyes upon [[Middle-earth]] again.<ref name="journey">{{S|3}}</ref>

He lived in [[Tirion]] for a while, where he also built the great, white tower at the topmost part of the city, called [[Mindon Eldaliéva]] or the Tower of Ingwë. It was never used, except by those who tended to the lamp at its summit.<ref>{{LR|Lhammas}}, p. 173</ref><ref group="note">This detail is only found in ''Quenta Noldorinwa'' and the ''Lhammas'' from the 1930s.</ref>

There he begot many children, as noted by Finwë when Finwë complained to the Valar about his widowhood.<ref>{{MR|P3II2}}, p. 206</ref>

At some point, however, he went to live on [[Taniquetil]] at the feet of [[Manwë]].<ref name="princes">{{S|5}}</ref>

[[Indis]], the second wife of [[Finwë]], was of his close kin.<ref>{{S|6}}</ref>

==Characteristics==
Ingwë is described as being tall and beautiful,<ref name="Gol" /> and his hair as golden and curly.<ref name="Cur" /> He is also said to have been "more given to thought than arts".<ref name="Gol" />

==Etymology==
{{Pronounce|Ingwe.mp3|Ardamir}}
The name ''Ingwë'' is in [[Quenya]]. It means "chief", being derived from the root [[ING]] ("highest", "top"), to which is attached the suffix ''[[-wë]]'' ("person").<ref name="Shib">{{PM|Finwe}}</ref>{{rp|340}}<ref>{{webcite|author=[[Paul Strack]]|articleurl=http://eldamo.org/content/words/word-2208467609.html|articlename=Q. ''Ingwë'' m.|website=Eldamo|accessed=20 April 2022}}</ref>

The Vanyar called themselves the ''Ingwer'', the chieftains, on account of being considered the leaders and principal kindred of the Eldar, and their king's proper title was '''''Ingwë Ingweron''''': ‘chief of the chieftains’.<ref name="Shib"/>{{rp|340}}

In the earlier [[The Etymologies|''Etymologies'']], ''Ingwë'' is said to be a compound of ''[[inga|ing]]'' ("first") + the ending ''[[-wë|-we]]'' ("man").<ref>{{LR|Etymologies}}, entries "ING", "WEG"</ref>

